# 🌊 Flood Prediction System Using Machine Learning

## 📌 Project Overview

Floods are among the most devastating natural disasters, causing significant loss of life, infrastructure damage, and economic disruption worldwide. Accurate and timely flood prediction is essential for minimizing risks and enabling effective disaster management.

This project presents a **Machine Learning-based Flood Prediction System** that analyzes historical meteorological data and predicts the likelihood of flood occurrence. The system utilizes multiple classification algorithms including:

* Decision Tree
* Random Forest
* K-Nearest Neighbours (KNN)
* XGBoost

After performance evaluation, the best-performing model (**XGBoost**) is integrated into a Flask web application for real-time flood risk prediction.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Predict flood occurrences using historical weather and rainfall data.
* Compare the performance of multiple machine learning algorithms.
* Identify the most influential rainfall features contributing to floods.
* Deploy the best-performing model through a user-friendly web application.
* Support disaster management authorities with early flood warnings.

---

## 🏗️ System Architecture

Dataset → Data Preprocessing → Feature Engineering → Model Training → Model Evaluation → Best Model Selection → Model Deployment (Flask) → Flood Prediction

---

## 📂 Dataset Description

The dataset contains historical rainfall records and flood occurrence information.

### Features

| Feature | Description                               |
| ------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| YEAR    | Observation Year                          |
| JAN-DEC | Monthly Rainfall Data                     |
| Jan-Feb | Rainfall during January-February          |
| Mar-May | Rainfall during March-May                 |
| Jun-Sep | Rainfall during June-September            |
| Oct-Dec | Rainfall during October-December          |
| ANNUAL  | Total Annual Rainfall                     |
| FLOODS  | Target Variable (0 = No Flood, 1 = Flood) |

